    "131327914": {
      "title": "CO 2 -induced climate change in CMIP2 experiments: Quantification of agreement and role of internal variability",
      "abstract": "Abstract CO2-induced changes in surface air temperature, precipitation, and sea level pressure are compared between model experiments participating in the second phase of the Coupled Model Intercomparison Project (CMIP2). A statistical formalism is applied, in which the average squared amplitude of the simulated climate changes is divided into a common signal and variances associated with internal variability and model differences. In the 20-yr period centered at the doubling of CO2 and for a set of 14–15 models, the dimensionless global relative agreement on gridbox-scale annual mean climate changes is 0.89 for surface air temperature but only 0.22 for precipitation and 0.46 for sea level pressure. A majority of the interexperiment differences are attributed to model differences; the contribution of internal variability to the differences in change is estimated as 16% for temperature, 34% for precipitation, and 32% for sea level pressure. For seasonal rather than annual climate changes, the agreement is ..."
